## Redis Caching

```go
// Rate limiting pattern
key := fmt.Sprintf("rate:%s:%s:%s", orgID, appID, endpointID)
count, err := redisClient.Incr(ctx, key).Result()
if count == 1 {
    redisClient.Expire(ctx, key, time.Minute)
}
```

## Rules

- Always include `organization_id` and `app_id` in tables
- Use `pgxpool.Pool` (not single connections)
- Handle `pgx.ErrNoRows` explicitly
- Use parameterized queries (`$1`, `$2`) - never string concatenation
- Add indexes for foreign keys and frequently queried columns

## Checklist

- [ ] Repository implements domain interface
- [ ] Multi-tenant columns included
- [ ] Migration has both Up and Down
- [ ] Indexes on foreign keys
- [ ] Error wrapping with `domainErr.New()`
- [ ] `pgx.ErrNoRows` handled for GetByID
